## 5. Precedence

**RISK-001-REQ-5.1:** Where this standard's governance floor for a unit of work conflicts with a lower requirement stated elsewhere (e.g., a RoleSpec that appears to permit unilateral action on something this standard classifies at R3 or above), this standard's floor governs. A RoleSpec MUST NOT be read as silently exempting a unit of work from its deterministic Risk Class.

**RISK-001-REQ-5.2:** The Constitution and Governance Handbook remain supreme over this standard on all matters of ultimate human authority; this standard operationalizes *how much process precedes* a decision, not *who* ultimately holds authority over it.

**RISK-001-REQ-5.3:** RES-001 and RES-002 remain supreme over this standard on matters of role structure and specification format; this standard consumes those mechanisms rather than redefining them (§4).

