## 7. Priority Independence (Elaboration)

This section elaborates §6.3 because conflating risk and priority was identified as a specific outcome this standard must prevent, and a single sentence in the philosophy section is not sufficient to make the separation operationally durable.

**RISK-001-REQ-7.1:** A POS work-item record MUST store Risk Class and Priority as two separate, independently-settable fields. No default computation may derive one from the other.

**RISK-001-REQ-7.2:** A RoleSpec or work-item template MUST NOT present Risk Class and Priority as a single combined field (e.g., a single "urgency" score). Where a role needs to reason about both together (e.g., PM sequencing high-priority, high-risk work), it MUST do so by reading both fields independently, not a derived composite.

**RISK-001-REQ-7.3:** Raising a unit of work's priority MUST NOT be used as a justification for lowering, bypassing, or expediting its governance floor. Urgency does not reduce required review, approval, evidence, or verification (§10); at most, urgency may justify parallelizing governance steps that do not have a sequencing dependency on each other, never omitting them.

