## 10. Governance Requirements

**RISK-001-REQ-10.1:** Each Risk Class carries a fixed governance floor across the following dimensions: required review, required approval, required evidence, required verification, escalation posture, rollback expectation, merge authority, deployment authority, and acceptance rules. These are floors: any RoleSpec or product-specific standard MAY impose additional requirements, but MUST NOT impose fewer than the applicable row below.

| Dimension | R0 | R1 | R2 | R3 | R4 | R5 |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| **Review** | None required | Self-review by acting role | Peer or Architect review | Independent Review mandatory (RES-002 §13.1) | Independent Review + Structural Review (RES-002 §20) | Independent Review + Structural Review + Constitutional Review (§11.4) |
| **Approval** | Acting role (implicit) | Acting role | Architect (technical) or PM (delivery), per domain | Architect approval mandatory; Founder INFORM | Founder approval mandatory (RES-002 §22.2 pattern) | Founder approval mandatory, no delegation permitted |
| **Evidence** | None required | Informal (commit message sufficient) | Test result or equivalent artifact (POS-RS §7.5) | Test result + dry-run output + data citation as applicable | Regression test evidence (RES-002 §21) + changelog | Regression test evidence + changelog + explicit rationale tied to constitutional principle affected |
| **Verification** | None | Author-asserted | Reviewer-asserted | Independent Reviewer verifies against Architect-defined acceptance criteria (ARCH-SPEC §6) | Structural Review verifies conformance to RES-002 §6/§20 | Same as R4, plus verification that no lower-tier document silently conflicts (§5.1) |
| **Escalation posture** | N/A | Self-resolve; escalate only if blocked | Escalate per role's Escalation Rules (RES-002 §16) if ambiguous | Any ambiguity escalates to Architect/Founder before proceeding | Any ambiguity escalates to Founder; no AI role may resolve unilaterally | Any ambiguity halts work pending Founder resolution; no default-forward path (§16.3 of RES-002 does not apply at R5) |
| **Rollback expectation** | Not applicable | Recommended, not mandatory | Mandatory rollback plan for infra/schema changes | Mandatory, tested rollback plan required before deployment | Mandatory documented reversion path (supersession per RES-001 §9) | Mandatory documented reversion path; reversion itself requires Founder approval at R5 |
| **Merge authority** | Acting role | Acting role, or PM per delivery norms | Architect or delegated reviewer | Founder only (per existing organizational practice) | Founder only | Founder only |
| **Deployment authority** | N/A | PM/Architect per existing delegation | Architect certifies readiness; Founder authorizes (ARCH-SPEC §3 pattern) | Founder authorizes; Architect certifies; Independent Review confirms | Founder authorizes; treated as a governance release (POS-RS §7.9) | Founder authorizes; treated as a constitutional amendment event |
| **Acceptance rules** | Self-accepted | Self-accepted or PM-accepted | Distinct acceptor from assignor if PM-SPEC/ARCH-SPEC scope applies | Distinct acceptor mandatory (RES-002 §13.1) | Distinct acceptor mandatory; Founder is final acceptor | Distinct acceptor mandatory; Founder is sole acceptor |

**RISK-001-REQ-10.2:** A unit of work MUST NOT proceed past any governance dimension's floor for its effective Risk Class without satisfying that dimension. Partial satisfaction (e.g., approval obtained but evidence missing) does not permit proceeding.

**RISK-001-REQ-10.3:** The table in §10.1 is itself an R4 artifact (§8.3); any change to a cell's requirement is a `MAJOR` amendment to this standard.

